
remove previous gazebo install:
>> sudo apt-get remove '.*gazebo.*' '.*sdformat.*' '.*ignition-math.*' '.*ignition-msgs.*' '.*ignition-transport.*'

install gazebo7:
>> sudo apt-get install gazebo7

install "gazebo_ros_pkgs" for ROS Kinetic:
>> sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-gazebo-ros-pkgs ros-kinetic-gazebo-ros-control

source ROS setup file:
>> source /opt/ros/kinetic/setup.bash
>> source ~/catkin_ws/devel/setup.bash

testing:
>> roscore
>> rosrun gazebo_ros gazebo





to start an empty gazebo world in ros:
>> roslaunch gazebo_ros empty_world.launch







install libfranca + franka_ros:
use this guide : https://frankaemika.github.io/docs/installation.html
section : building from source:
first build libfranka and get its path to the build folder, using the commands "pwd" is useful
then build the ROS packages:
and for this you will need the path to the libfranka you got in previous step


to add folders to the ROS_PACKAGE_PATH:
>> gedit ~/.bashrc

add these lines:
>> export ROS_PACKAGE_PATH=/home/work/catkin_ws/src:/opt/ros/kinetic/stacks:$ROS_PACKAGE_PATH






install allegro hand ros package:
- first we need to install libpcan ros packages:
>>catkin/src/ git clone https://github.com/ipa320/cob_extern.git

>>catkin/src/ git clone https://github.com/simlabrobotics/allegro_hand_ros.git

>>catkin/ catkin_make







